cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "AQR: Auto Quant Research"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Vadim
    family-names: Rybalko
    orcid: ""
repository-code: "https://github.com/vadryb13/aqr"
abstract: >-
  AQR is an open-source LLM-driven quantitative research framework for
  MOEX (Moscow Exchange) markets. It generates trading hypotheses at scale,
  backtests them with rigorous statistical corrections (Deflated Sharpe Ratio,
  Combinatorial Purged Cross-Validation, Probability of Backtest Overfitting),
  and accumulates validated knowledge in a hierarchical memory system.
keywords:
  - quantitative-finance
  - moex
  - llm-agents
  - backtest
  - deflated-sharpe
  - cpcv
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-07-10
